[0.011, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[38;2;215;119;87m в–җ\u001b[48;2;0;0;0mв–ӣв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–ң\u001b[49mв–Ң\u001b[3C\u001b[39m\u001b[1mClaude\u001b[1CCode\u001b[1C\u001b[22m\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mv2.1.84\u001b[39m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;215;119;87mв–қв–ң\u001b[48;2;0;0;0mв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳ\u001b[49mв–ӣв–ҳ\u001b[2C\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mOpus\u001b[1C4.6\u001b[1C(1M\u001b[1Ccontext)\u001b[1CВ·\u001b[1CClaude\u001b[1CMax\u001b[39m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;215;119;87m \u001b[1Cв–ҳв–ҳ\u001b[1Cв–қв–қ\u001b[4C\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m~/projects/talks/oreilly-codecon-march-2026/demo-4\u001b[39m\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;136;136;136mв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\u001b[39m\r\r\nвқҜВ \u001b[7m \u001b[27m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;136;136;136mв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ"]
[0.000, "o", "в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\u001b[39m\r\r\n\u001b[2C\u001b[38;2;255;107;128mвҸөвҸө\u001b[1Cbypass\u001b[1Cpermissions\u001b[1Con\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m (shift+tab\u001b[1Cto\u001b[1Ccycle)\u001b[80Cв—җ\u001b[1Cmedium\u001b[1CВ·\u001b[1C/effort\u001b[39m\r\r\n\u001b[2C\u001b[3A\u001b[?2026l"]
[0.044, "o", "\u001b]0;в Ӯ Claude Code\u0007"]
[0.014, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[2D\u001b[3B\r\u001b[4A\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;80;80;80mвқҜ \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mYou have a working bookmarks manager app called \"Link Shelf\" with Express and SQLite. Read the existing code files (db.js, validation.js, \u001b[39m       \r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mserver.js, test.js) and the AGENTS.md file to understand the codebase.\u001b[39m                                                                             \r\u001b[1B                                                                                                                                                   \r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mYour task: Add a FAVORITES feature to Link Shelf using Agent Teams with QUALITY GATES enforced.\u001b[39m                                                    \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m## Quality Gate 1: Plan Approval\u001b[39m                                           "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                        \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mBefore writing ANY code, create a detailed plan for adding favorites. The plan must include:\u001b[39m                                                       \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m- Database changes needed (schema migration)\u001b[39m                                                                                                       \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m- New API endpoints\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m- Validation rules\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                 \u001b"]
[0.000, "o", "[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m- Test cases\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                       \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mSubmit the plan for review. Think critically about the plan вҖ” if it's missing a migration step for existing databases (ALTER TABLE to add an \u001b[39m      \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mis_favorite column), the plan should be revised to include it. This is a common mistake: you can't just define a column in CREATE TABLE if the \u001b[39m    \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mtable already exists with data.\u001b[39m                                                                                                                    \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m                                                "]
[0.001, "o", "                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m## Quality Gate 2: Implementation with Hooks\u001b[39m                                                                                                       \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mImplement the favorites feature:\u001b[39m                                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m1. Add is_favorite column to links table (ALTER TABLE migration for existing data)\u001b[39m                                                                 \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m2. Add PUT /api/links/:id/favorite endpoint to toggle favorites\u001b[39m                                                          "]
[0.001, "o", "                          \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m3. Add GET /api/links/favorites endpoint to filter favorites only\u001b[39m                                                                                  \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m4. Add tests for all favorites operations\u001b[39m                                                                                                          \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mAfter implementation, run these quality checks (simulating TaskCompleted hooks):\u001b[39m                                                                   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m- Run `npm test` вҖ” ALL tests must pass\u001b[39m                                                                                                             \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m- "]
[0.000, "o", "Run `grep -rn \"console.log\" --include=\"*.js\" --exclude=\"test.js\" .` вҖ” there must be NO console.log in production code (test.js is excluded)\u001b[39m      \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m- If either check fails, fix the issue and re-run checks until both pass\u001b[39m                                                                           \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m## Quality Gate 3: Compound Learning\u001b[39m                                                                                                               \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mAfter all tasks pass, update AGENTS.md with new learnings from this session. Add entries like:\u001b[3"]
[0.000, "o", "9m                                                     \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m- Migration patterns (always use ALTER TABLE for existing tables)\u001b[39m                                                                                  \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m- Any mistakes caught by hooks and how to avoid them\u001b[39m                                                                                               \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m- New conventions discovered\u001b[39m                                                                                                                       \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mThese learnings will help future agent sessions avoid the same mistakes.\u001b[39m                                                                           \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;"]
[0.000, "o", "55;55m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mIMPORTANT: Show the plan review process explicitly in your output. Show the hook checks running and their results. Show the AGENTS.md update at \u001b[39m   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mthe end.\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                           \u001b[49m\r\r\n\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;215;119;87mВ·\u001b[1CGitifyingвҖҰ\u001b[39m\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;136;136;136mв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ"]
